    "narrative": "Today\u2019s lineup for the Austin Waves is anchored by the explosive matchup potential of **Gunnar Henderson**, who earns our highest efficiency score of 74.06. Facing Warren, W, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a massive platoon advantage and the premium leadoff spot, providing the ideal catalyst for our core categories. Similarly, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (72.39) and **Drake Baldwin** (71.82) are high-priority starts; **Drake Baldwin** in particular benefits from a favorable 5.47 xERA matchup against Quintana, making him a sneaky source of production in the catcher slot. We are also monitoring **Josh Lowe** (71.68) closely as he faces Scott, who carries a brutal 15.44 xERA\u2014a massive opportunity for **Josh Lowe** to provide value even while batting lower in the order.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision involved keeping **Josh Jung** (56.18) on the bench. While **Josh Jung** carries a respectable projection against Flaherty, the marginal efficiency edge held by **Nolan Schanuel** (60.11) and **Miguel Vargas** (58.79) kept him out of the starting nine. **Miguel Vargas** remains in the fold despite a slight park penalty, as his strong SP skill rating against the 5.12 xERA of M\u00e1rquez keeps his floor higher than the alternatives. Conversely, **Heliot Ramos** (59.03) is a tactical play today; while facing a tough arm in McClanahan, his elite sprint speed gives us the SB upside we desperately require, and the projection model rewards his aggressive base-running environment.\n\nRisks remain focused on the lower-tier matchups, specifically for **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (57.72), who faces a stiff test against Misiorowski. While his platoon advantage is significant, his low SP skill score warns of a potential ceiling-capped performance. We are comfortable with **Kyle Tucker** (70.80) and **Andy Pages** (60.90) despite the left-on-left disadvantage against Liberatore, as their baseline hitting profiles remain resilient. We continue to hold **Marcell Ozuna**, **Brady House**, **Coby Mayo**, **Luis Robert Jr.**, **Jackson Merrill**, **Jordan Westburg**, **Jorge Polanco**, **Nasim Nunez**, **Dominic Smith**, and **Liam Hicks** in reserve, prepared to pivot if weather patterns shift or lineup volatility necessitates a late-afternoon adjustment to the bench strategy.",
